                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding-bottom: 8px; padding-top: 8px;" onclick="if(this.parentNode.parentNode.rows.item(1).style.display==''){this.parentNode.parentNode.rows.item(1).style.display='none';this.style.backgroundImage='url(images/static/col.gif)'}else{this.parentNode.parentNode.rows.item(1).style.display='';this.style.backgroundImage='url(images/static/exp.gif)'}" class="heading"><span style="color: #196297;">Why should I add FAQs to my website?</span></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="display: none;" class="fact">
                        <td class="fact">FAQ (Frequently Asked Question) pages have become commonplace on many websites. One of the biggest reasons is that they offer a way to provide self support so that customers and prospects can solve their own issues that come up.&nbsp;For larger companies,&nbsp;good FAQ pages can significantly decrease the&nbsp;demand&nbsp;on support and sales staff.<br>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
